tan\n4:00 Erskine Johnson*\n4:15 The Johnson Family*\n4:30 Melody Hour*\n5:00 Pete Howe*\n5:15 Superman*\n5:30 Captain Midnight*\n5:45 Tom Mix*\nMANY NEVER\nSUSPECT CAUSE\nOF BACKACHES\nThis Old Treatment Often\nBrings Happy Relief\nMany striferers relieve Banins baekaehe\ntjuiekiy. onee they discover that t he real cause\ncf their trouble may be tired kidneys.\nThe kidneys are Nature's chief way of tak\ning; the excess acids and waste out of the blood.\nThey help most people pass about 3 pints a day.\nWhen disorder of kidney function permits\npoisonous matter to remain in your blood, it\nmay cause nagging backache, rheumatic\npains. leg pains, loss of pep and energy, get\nting up nights, swelling, pufiness under the\neyes, headaches and dizziness. Frequent or\nscanty passages with smarting and burning\nsometimes shown there k something wrong\nwith your kidneys or bladder.\nDon't wait! Ask your druggist for Dean\u2019s\nFills, a stimulant diuretic, used successfully\nby millions for over 40 years. Doan\u2019s give\nhappy relief and wiU help the 15 miles of I\nkidney tubes flush out poisonous waste from\nyour blood. Get Doan\u2019s Fills.\nKEY WEST IN i\nDAYS GONE BY\nFROM FILES OF THE CITIZEN\nOF DECEMBER 13. 1935\nRoland Craig, who owns sev\neral business places on the keys\nand whose residence is at Craig,\nFlorida, is a visitor in Key West\ntodav.\nMr. and Mrs. Leland Carey.\n1118 Olivia street, announced to\nday the birth of a nine-pound\nson last night.\nMiss Florence Sawyer. 523\nEaton street, will entertain the j\nKey West Coral Wheel Club at\nher home tonight.\nKey West Junior Woman's\nI Club, at a meeting last night,\nmade final arrangements for i\nthe Christmas tree for needy\nchildren. The tree will be decor\nrated and ready for display at\n3 o\u2019clock in the afternoon on\n4 V V flCs HBhS \u25a0tjj\nMon',\n,11 |l O' MM M MO\nPOLLOCK\u2019S\nQUAUTY JEWELERS\n524 Southard Street Opposite Bus Station\nSee Our Window\nDecember 23 at the Coral Isle\nCasino.\nSecretary Edna Wilson of the\nHarris School Parent-Teachei\nAssociation, said today tnat it\nis the only organizaton of its\nkind in the thirteenth district\nof Florida that has been placed\non the honor roll of the stale fo:\nthe payment of all dues.\nA football game will be played\nin Bay-view Park Saturday after\nnoon, beginning at 2 o'clock.\nA. Maitland Adams, manager\nof the Thompson Enterprises,\nwho had been on a business visit\nin Miami, returned yesterday.\nForrest Gav returned this\nmorning from a short visit in\nMiami.\nCaptain Philip Cosgrove, >1\nthe lighthouse tender Ivy. n\nbv plane this morning\nfrom Miami.\nToday The Citizen says in an\neditorial paragraph:\n\u201cBorrowing mav seem easy,\nbut paying back isn't sport.*'\nTHURSP \\y. PE r FM7TT! n. 194 4\nNEW LOW' RATE\nXew Y \u2019rk\u2014Pan Ammrjpi Air\nways has oegur. anew lew sate\ntrans Atlantic sen ice The first\nplane took orf for L,indan mith\n24 pass' nLTs. The Lit was 5273\none wav round trip Pre\nvtous'v the rate ma- >572 one\nBolivia's president net difi*\nbo FALSE TEETH\nKetk. STTJe or Slip?\nFArrr.rrH m\nbe 1n r- lp%T fair*.\nlIT r^hrlm\nTKt.ni u MJmm Dmemwm*\nfns\u201d. Cr< O or\u201d taritrr\nt- a -I), c-. r-ur.. t n ui tw\n\u2022t are.\nSEWING MACHINES\nEXPERT REPAIRING\nHome A i jus \u2018.meat Seme*\nY\u2019.,. r.\nTel After 5 P. M","height":"26550","width":"20844"}}
